                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Θεμίσων">Θεμίσων</name> <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63108"><name nymRef="#Ἄριστις" type="patronymic">Ἀρίστιος</name></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Asklepios"><name nymRef="#Ἀσκλαπιός">Ἀσκλα<supplied reason="lost">πι</supplied>ῶι</name></persName> <w lemma="ἀνατίθημι">ἀνέθηκε</w>.
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Thémison fils d'Aristis a consacré à Asclè<supplied reason="lost">pi</supplied>os.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p>Themison son of Aristis dedicated to Askle<supplied reason="lost">pi</supplied>os.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
                <p>Themison figlio di Aristis ha dedicato ad Ascle<supplied reason="lost">pi</supplied>o.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The funerary base of the dedicant is <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr077800</ref> in tomb E121.</p>
